definition.value: A cholestanoyl-CoA formed by thioester linkage between 3alpha,7alpha-dihydroxy-5beta-cholestan-26-oic acid and coenzyme A.
A glycosyl alditol consisting of alpha-D-galactofuranosyl and D-galactitol residues joined in sequence by a (1->2) glycosidic bond.
A multi-methyl-branched fatty acyl-CoA that is the S-(4,8,12-trimethyltridecanoyl) derivative of coenzyme A.
An  aminobutanoyl-CoA resulting from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxylic acid group of 4-aminobutanoic acid.
A glycosylxylose consisting of a beta-D-glucopyranose residue and a D-xylopyranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->5) glycosidic bond.
The S-(trans-4-carboxybut-2-enoyl) derivative of coenzyme A.
A glycosylgalactose consisting of an alpha-D-glucopyranose residue and a D-galactopyranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->2) glycosidic bond.
A chlorobenzoyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 4-chlorobenzoic acid
